===Noun===
'''archea'''
{{wikipedia}}

#(Biology)A group of single celled life, lacking [[nucleus|nuclei]] (and hence [[prokaryote]]s).  These are some of the most primitive (least changed) forms of life.   Archaea, Eukaryotes and Bacteria are the fundamental classifications in what is called the three-domain system of [[taxonomy]].  They are known as [[Monera]] in the five kingdom taxonomy.

